IMPACT SUBRCB
Yash Dayal
KD Karthik

9.45pm A heartening comeback for RCB with a 95-run stand off just 57 balls, but their middle overs were almost disastrous when they kept losing wickets and went 28 balls without a boundary. They have got themselves a fighting chance, but CSK will be the happier side. DK says he was a bit rusty. "Right till the end, I was just fighting my form. I was rusty, I was trying hard, Anuj, young boy, played a special knock. It is a very very good pitch for batting. I wouldn't be surprised if we are a bit under-par. We will have to field very well and bowl out of our skins. The last over, he bowled really well, but I couldn' mconnect at all. If I could have hit one six that would be the difference between 182-183 and the 173 we got. But if we field well, which we are capable of, and looks like I won't be there so even better, we can fight."

That DK interview tells you what we have been suspecting: that this is a good pitch and that CSK had caused enough damage in the middle overs. Mustafizur was atbthe forefornt of it with four wickets in his first two overs, but the spinners also shut RCB down. Ashish Pant will bring you the chase.

7.40pm Faf du Plessis has won the toss, and RCB are batting first. "Generally it is always a bat-first wicket," says du Plessis, who knows the ground well as a former CSK player.

Gaikwad says he came to know he would be the captain a week ago. CSK's four overseas players are Rachin Ravindra, Daryl Mitchell, Maheesh Theekshana and Mustafizur Rahamn. He also says Sameer Rizvi is making his debut.

7.35pm Conditions report time. Brian Lara says there are a few cracks, and there is some looseness on the edges of the crack. Lara feels spin is going to play a part. I think they are playing on the centre strip because there is no one boundary that is bigger. Lara still feels you bowl first despite the expectation of spin because you want to protect them from the dew.

7.30pm The toss has been delayed to 7.40pm even though the captains have been out and ready. The start time stays at 8pm.

Deivarayan Mathu has seen Alzarri Joseph mark his run-up. Like Faf du Plessis, Joseph is also a Super Kings man, who unfortunately will play against them in the IPL. Deivarayan points out how du Plessis has liked to play Joseph both for St Lucia Kings and Joburg Super Kings.

7.25pm All eyes on two men who haven't played in a while. Virat Kohli more so because not just RCB fans but also India fans want to see how he responds to the latest demands the India team seems to have made of him in T20 cricket. And MS Dhoni of course, who has again found a way to surprise people after all these years.

6.30pm If you want to know what's it like at Chepauk right now, Deiva sets it up beautifully from the venue. "He has handed over captaincy to Gaikwad, but he's still Chennai's Thala. The chants of "Dhoni!Dhoni!Dhoni!" and the whistles for him are getting louder and louder. It looks very much like these 14 matches - 16 or 17 if luck is once again on his side - are very much the beginning of the end. At the same time, the crowd is warming up to the new captain Gaikwad. Once, another Gaikwad with Maharashtrian roots, a certain Shivaji Rao, went on to become a household name in Chennai. That's some way away, but for now Gaikwad has the keys to the Chennai kingdom. A huge replica of the IPL trophy now makes its way into the middle. The LED lights are also being tested out ahead of the opening ceremony, which will include performances of AR Rahman and Prabhu Deva."

6.25pm The last time CSK and RCB played the opening game of an IPL season, RCB were rolled over for 70, and it took CSK 17.4 overs to chase the target down. RCB will want to right that wrong. But can they? CSK have three spin options in Maheesh Theekshana, Ravindra Jadeja and part-timer Rachin Ravindra on what could be another slow pitch. In contrast, RCB don't have a world-class spinner in their ranks. Here's Deivarayan Muthu with the match preview.

Pawas: "The first true transitional season of IPL is about to kick off" Really feels that way, isn't? The first time ever in the IPL that none of Virat Kohli, Rohit Sharma or MS Dhoni will be leading a team.

6.10pm We are still close to two hours away from ball one, but Chepauk is already half full and it shouldn't take long for the stadium to be packed to the rafters. And make no mistake, it's going to be a sea of Yellow at the Chepauk. There will be an opening ceremony with all the glitz and glamour in full flow. Once the dust settles, RCB will try and get the better of CSK at a venue where they haven't had a lot of success. In fact, just once in nine attempts - that one coming way back in 2008. Can they change history?

Afeef: "And so begins another season of the IPL. Looking forward to a fantastic season. May or not be Dhoni's last, but we know he will get the loudest cheer everywhere he goes."

5.55pm There is a also a small matter of Virat Kohli returning to competitive cricket after close to two-and-a-half months having missed India's five-game Test series against England. His most recent game was a T20I against Afghanistan in mid-January. How he goes in Chennai will be interesting to see, especially with the T20 World Cup starting right after the IPL.

5.40pm Righto, where do we start. The latest captaincy change is a good place, I reckon. A day before the IPL begins, defending champions CSK have a new captain - Ruturaj Gaikwad. Yep. And as with most things with Dhoni: It happened quietly. A whisper into the ether. Just like it did in 2014. And then in 2020. The end of an era. MS Dhoni's last act as captain was lifting the IPL trophy. His most lasting act, subverting expectation. Here's Alagappan Muthu on how as a season begins, an era ends, but life goes on for Dhoni.

5.30pm IPL S17 E01. Ten months on since that crazy final in Ahmedabad which started on a Sunday and ended on a Tuesday, we are back it again. Ten venues. Ten teams. New captains. Comebacks. Fanwars. The carnival returns. Hello and welcome to the ball-by-ball commentary of match No. 1 of IPL 2024 - MS Dhoni Ruturaj Gaikwad-led CSK vs Faf du Plessis-led RCB. I am Ashish Pant nice and early and will soon be joined by Sidharth Monga with all that unfolds in Chennai. Join in, it's going to be a fun ride.
